President Muhammadu Buhari has thanked General Theophilus Yakubu Danjuma, Rtd, for his lifetime devotion to humanitarian causes and kindness to the less privileged in the society. Buhari hailed the former Army General on the occasion of his 83rd birthday. In a statement signed and made available to DAILY POST by his Spokesman, Garba Shehu, Buhari recounts General Danjuma’s record of service and dedication to the Nigerian Armed Forces as well as many other fields of endeavour in the country, “thanking him for his lifetime devotion to humanitarian causes and kindness to the less privileged in the society.” Buhari prayed the almighty God to sustain the elder statesman with health and happiness in the years ahead.